FBIS3-53301 "drnes009_p_94002" FBIS-NES-94-009 Document Type:Daily Report 13 Jan 1994 SOUTH ASIA Afghanistan Iranian Envoy Expresses Hope of Cease-Fire LD1201172294 Tehran IRIB Television First Program Network in Persian 1530 GMT 12 Jan 94 LD1201172294 Tehran IRIB Television First Program Network Language: Persian Article Type:BFN [Excerpt] [passage omitted] The efforts of the Islamic Republic of Iran to prevent a resumption of hostilities and fratricide in Afghanistan continue. The Foreign Ministry has announced that the Islamic Republic government's special envoy to Afghanistan, who delivered a message from President Hashemi- Rafsanjani, expressed the hope this morning, after meetings with Afghan President Rabbani, Prime Minister Hekmatyar, and other leaders of that country, that within the next 48 hours cease-fire arrangements will be implemented. He added: At the meetings, the Afghan leaders expressed their appreciation for the Islamic Republic's peace efforts and their wish for an end to clashes in Afghanistan.
